snippet.textDisplay: I do not know where the first few lines came from, but ‘anokha ladka khelan ko maange chaand’, it actually refers to when Krishna, looking in the reflection of the moon in a water vessel, demands the moon as his toy. And then his mother Yashoda says- what a wondrous child, wants to play with the moon! It is a spectacular rendition, but I find the rest of the lyrics about non-platonic love a little confusing in a mother-son song. Did anyone else notice this? Anokha ladka isn’t originally like this.
